msgid "The scans and character recognition (OCR) of the books have been completed.  Occurrence data must now be extracted from those sources and compiled in a spreadsheet format."
msgstr "Se han completado los escaneos y el reconocimiento de caracteres (OCR) de los libros. Los datos de registros biológicos ahora deben extraerse de esas fuentes y compilarse en un formato de hoja de cálculo."

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:96
msgid "The original data was in German and, to make it more widely usable when published online, the project manager would like to make it available in English."
msgstr "Los datos originales estaban en alemán y, para facilitar su uso cuando se publiquen en línea, el director del proyecto desea que estén disponibles en inglés."

#. Do not translate this block
#. The {empty} is to prevent the "2." producing a numbered list.
#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:101
msgid "{empty}2. Cerchneis tinnunculus, Linn. ( \"Taarnfalk\") nests in several steeples around Viborg."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:103
msgid "At the churches of Mönsted and Daubjerg there were several family groups in 1880, each of 7 individuals, suggesting a particularly abundant source of food on the surrounding heather (lizards). In the area of Thisted, where the tower falcon broods very often, young were always present in broods of 6, only once did I find a group of 7 on Egebäksande (H.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:105
msgid "In Horsens I found kestrels brooding on the churches of Vähr, Hansted, Hundslund, Thyrsted and Oelsted. In the steeple of Vähr I found a nest with 6 eggs on 6 May 1875, 6 eggs on 30 April 1876, 4 eggs on 28 April 1878; in 1877 and 1879 there were none, on 2 May 1880 they had 5 eggs, in 1882 also 5 eggs, and in 1883 seven."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:107
msgid "In Oelsted 5 eggs on 3 May 1879, in 1882 also 5, and in 1883 6 eggs."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:109
msgid "On the churches (Our Lady’s and St. Peter’s) of Copenhagen, I have often seen it in the autumn and winter of 1879; in spring 1880, it brooded on Our Lady’s church, the \"round tower\" and the law firm building (in a valve) and certainly also on St. Peter's Church. (F.)"
msgstr ""

#. End block - Begin translation again
#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:115
msgid "Take the role of a volunteer charged with transforming the translated text into a spreadsheet as individual occurrences.  The occurrences will need unique numbers assigned to them."
msgstr "Asuma el rol de un voluntario encargado de transformar el texto traducido en una hoja de cálculo como registros biológicos individuales. Los registros biológicos necesitarán que se les asignen números únicos."

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:116
msgid "Create a spreadsheet using the data fields listed in the <<birds-digital-data-description>> using data found in the example above recorded by: Chr. Fr. Lütken."
msgstr "Cree una hoja de cálculo utilizando los campos de datos enumerados en la <<birds-digital-data-description>> utilizando los datos encontrados en el ejemplo anterior registrados por: Chr. P. Lütken."

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:117
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-lepidoptera-sampling.adoc:86
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-marine.adoc:25
msgid "Use the exercise sheet to provide your answers and submit the spreadsheet created in the previous step."
msgstr "Use la hoja de ejercicios para proporcionar sus respuestas y envíe la hoja de cálculo creada en el paso previo."

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:119
msgid "In the examples used, the individual occurrences do not always contain data to complete all of the columns in the spreadsheet."
msgstr "En los ejemplos utilizados, los registros biológicos individuales no siempre contienen datos para completar todas las columnas de la hoja de cálculo."

